results.name: Triangle read by rows in which T(n,k) is the sum of the k-th largest elements in all overpartitions of n.
comment: It appears that T(n,k) is also the total number of parts >= k in all overpartitions of n.
It appears that the first differences of row n together with 2 give row n of triangle A235798.
The equivalent sequence for partitions is A181187.
results.author: _Omar E. Pol_, Jan 18 2014
